message.content: If someone writes ten notes per day using Harmony's handmade notepads, each made from five letter-size sheets of paper folded three times and stapled together, the duration for which the notepad will last would depend on the size of the notes being written. Assuming that each note takes up one sheet of paper (i.e., one of Harmony's folded pieces), then the notepad would have a total of 15 sheets or 30 sides available for writing. Since ten notes are being written per day, this means that it would take approximately three and a half days (3.5) to fill up the entire notepad. Therefore, the notepad would last for around three and a half days before needing to be refilled or replaced with a new one.
